For older releases, go to:
https://github.com/clyde80/i3-configuration/releases

Logging started on November 08, 2016

Changes in Minimal Red theme
    - February 24, 2017

1. Updated gifenc script
    - Allow user to specify the width of the resulting GIF.
    - Allow user to specify the FPS of the resulting GIF.

----- Date: February 23, 2017 -----

1. Change script headers to be consistent.
2. Change script usage messages to be consistent.

----- Date: February 17, 2017 -----

1. Add makealbum script to scripts directory.

----- Date: February 12, 2017 -----

1. Changed coding syntax in scripts.
    - Using "[[" instead of "[".
        - getmusicstatus, getvolume, getwifinetwork, rmemptydirs, sao
    - Usage message in code is much cleaner.
        - getmusicstatus, getvolume, getwifinetwork, rmemptydirs, sao
    - Added directions for dealing with bugs.
        - getmusicstatus, getvolume, getwifinetwork, rmemptydirs, sao
    - Updates to individual scripts.
        - getvolume 
            - Added support for HDMI.
            - Changed coding style to have constants for each device.
                - 1 = speakers, 2 = headphones, 3 = HDMI.
        - rmemptydirs
            - Modified code to disiplay help message.
        
----- Date: February 07, 2017 -----

1. Changed main colors to Red, Orange and Black.

2. Changed main font to "ypn envypn".
    - This is a bitmap font. To use bitmap fonts in Firefox,
      set gfx.font_rendering.fontconfig.fontlist.enabled to false in about:config.

3. Changes to CMUS
    - Removed some lines and highlighting.
    - Changed status line for CMUS to display music selection as well as time.

4. Changes to Scripts
    - Changed PS1 in ~/.bashrc.
        - Now displays as "user@host $PWD >> "
    - Removed iconic characters from all scripts that are used in yabar.
        - monitor_workspaces.py
            - [#] denotes the focused workspace.
            - <#> denotes the urgent workspace.
            - # denotes a workspace number.
        - getmusicstatus
            - Thanks @johnfraney for fixing the "tag artistsort" bug.
        - battery
        - getwifinetwork
            - Changed status for connected to "OK" and not connected to "NOT OK".
        - getvolume
            - S means speakers and H means headphones.
    - Added condition in rrename.sh so it doesn't mess up your system.
    - NOTE: To get older versions of these scripts without these changes,
            see the file "/scripts/older_versions/Scripts.i3conf.v11.zip"

5. Changes to Yabar configuration.
    - Workspaces are now shown on the left.
    - Increased size of music display area.
    - Got rid of icons for date and time.

5. Changes to VIM configuration
    - Turned off line numbering for minimal purposes.
    - Sort of organized the "minimal.vim" file.

6. Changes to Firefox configuration
    - Created Stylish theme for Firefox.
        - Stylish theme for Turbo Download Manager will be made later (promise).
    - Modified homepage.
        - Got rid of buttons and made them links.
        - Homepage content now displays in the middle of browser window.
          No static values are used to try and do that now.

7. Changes in i3 config file.
    - Window borders are now 3px #161916.

8. Changes to xfce4-terminal
    - minimal.theme created.

9. Changes to project
    - Will start including the background image in repository.

10. Changes to README.md
    - Added link to "envypn" font.

